.\" Manpage for wxSolitaire.
.\" Content adapted from the bundled Solitaire Help (wxsolitairechm).
.TH WXSOLITAIRE 6 "2026-04-19" "wxSolitaire 1.0" "Games Manual"
.SH NAME
wxSolitaire \- classic Klondike Solitaire card game
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wxSolitaire
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wxSolitaire
is a cross-platform implementation of classic Klondike Solitaire built with
C++ and wxWidgets.
The object of the game is to use all the cards in the deck to build up the
four suit stacks from Ace to King.
.PP
The playing area has three regions:
.TP
.B Deck
Located in the upper left of the playing area.
Cards are drawn from the deck and moved to the suit and row stacks.
Depending on the \fBDraw\fR option, one or three cards are turned over at a
time.
When the deck is exhausted, clicking to the left of the deck turns it over
so drawing can continue.
.TP
.B Suit stacks
Four stacks in the upper right of the playing area, initially empty.
Suit stacks are built in ascending order, starting with the Ace.
An Ace can be moved only to an empty suit stack.
.TP
.B Row stacks
Seven stacks below the deck and suit stacks.
The number of cards per stack grows from one to seven, left to right;
the top card of each row stack is face up and the rest are face down.
Row stacks are built in descending order, alternating red and black
(light and dark on a monochrome display).
A King is the only card that can be moved to an empty row stack.
If a face-down card is uncovered, it can be turned face up.
.PP
The game is won when all four suit stacks have been built from Ace to King
using every card in the deck.
.SH PLAYING THE GAME
.SS Moving a card with the mouse
Drag the card from the deck or a stack to the target location and release
the mouse button.
To move multiple cards from a row stack, drag the uppermost card to be
moved.
Double-clicking a card in a row stack moves it to a suit stack when the
move is legal.
.SS Moving a card with the keyboard
.IP 1. 4
Press \fBTab\fR to move to the deck or a stack.
.IP 2. 4
Press \fBLeft\fR or \fBRight\fR to select a card, then \fBEnter\fR or
\fBSpace\fR to pick it up.
To move more than one card, use \fBUp\fR to extend the selection to the
uppermost card, then press \fBEnter\fR or \fBSpace\fR.
.IP 3. 4
If moving a card from the deck, press \fBTab\fR to jump to the suit or row
stacks, choose the destination with \fBLeft\fR or \fBRight\fR, and confirm
with \fBEnter\fR or \fBSpace\fR.
.SS Undo
Choose \fBGame\fR \(-> \fBUndo\fR (\fBCtrl+Z\fR) to cancel the last card
move or the last draw from the deck.
.SS Turning over cards
Click a face-down card, or select it with \fBTab\fR plus \fBLeft\fR /
\fBRight\fR and press \fBEnter\fR or \fBSpace\fR.
The \fBDraw One\fR option turns over a single card at a time; the
\fBDraw Three\fR option turns over three.
.SS Turning over the deck
Click to the left of the deck, or select that space with the arrow keys
and press \fBEnter\fR or \fBSpace\fR.
Under Standard scoring, 20 points are deducted for each pass through the
deck after three passes in Draw Three mode, or 100 points for each pass
after one pass in Draw One mode.
.SS Starting a new game
Choose \fBGame\fR \(-> \fBDeal\fR (\fBF2\fR).
.SH KEYBOARD
.TP
.B Tab
Move among the deck, suit stacks, and row stacks.
Tab selects a stack only when it is applicable to the next move.
.TP
.B Left, Right
Move to the next stack.
.TP
.B Up, Down
Move from card to card within a stack.
.TP
.B Enter, Space
Pick up and release a card or a group of cards.
Also turns over a card in the deck or a stack, and turns over the deck
itself.
.TP
.B F1
Open this help.
.TP
.B F2
Start a new game.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Z
Undo the last move.
.SH CARD DESIGN
Choose \fBGame\fR \(-> \fBCard Backs\fR and double-click the design you
want, or select a design with the arrow keys and press \fBEnter\fR.
Card designs can be changed at any time.
.SH SCORING
wxSolitaire offers two scoring systems \(em Standard and Vegas.
Scoring can also be turned off.
Changing the scoring option mid-game ends the current game and deals a
new one.
.SS Standard scoring
Points are earned based on time and the moves made.
A timed game grants a bonus on completion \(em the shorter the game, the
larger the bonus.
Timing can be disabled.
.TP
.B +10
Each card moved to a suit stack.
.TP
.B +5
Each card moved from the deck to a row stack.
.TP
.B -15
Each card moved from a suit stack to a row stack.
.TP
.B -20
Each pass through the deck after three passes (Draw Three).
.TP
.B -100
Each pass through the deck after one pass (Draw One).
.SS Vegas scoring
The ante is 52 dollars per game.
The object is to earn back more than the ante.
No time penalty or bonus is applied.
If \fBKeep Score\fR is enabled in the Options dialog, a running total is
kept from game to game.
.TP
.B +$5
Each card moved to a suit stack.
.PP
To reset the Vegas score to 52 dollars, switch the scoring option to
\fBNone\fR or \fBStandard\fR, press \fBEnter\fR, then re-select
\fBVegas\fR and press \fBEnter\fR again.
.SH OPTIONS
Choose \fBGame\fR \(-> \fBOptions\fR to change gameplay settings.
.SS Draw
.TP
.B Draw One
Turn over the top card of the deck.
.TP
.B Draw Three
Turn over three cards at a time.
.SS Scoring
\fBStandard\fR, \fBVegas\fR, or none.
.SS Display
.TP
.B Timed Game
Track the time elapsed during a game.
.TP
.B Status Bar
Show the status bar with score and time.
.TP
.B Keep Score
Keep a running total across games when using Vegas scoring.
.TP
.B Outline Dragging
Drag an outline of the card and recolour the destination when the move is
valid, rather than dragging the full bitmap.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/wxSolitaire/wxsolitaire.help
Help bundle containing the HTML help content.
.TP
.I /usr/share/wxSolitaire/wxsolitaire.chm
Windows compiled HTML Help file (for reference; open with xchm or a
compatible viewer).
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/wxSolitaire.desktop
Desktop-entry file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/wxSolitaire
Per-user settings saved between sessions.
